////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

NOTE: These are rules that govern that was curor funcitons within this project.

codename

c_1a__ structure      - Required codename structure.
c_1a_1    format      - Use snake_case (underscore between terms) for all codenames in code, files, and folders.
c_1a_2    term        - Use single word without spaces or special characters for each term in codename.
c_1a_3    root        - Start codename with approved root term that indicates type or purpose.

c_1b__ terms          - Rules for selecting terms.
c_1b_1    length      - Keep each term under 15 letters to maintain readability and prevent wrapping.
c_1b_2    case        - Write all letters in lowercase, no uppercase or mixed case allowed in any term.
c_1b_3    verb        - Use present tense base verbs (get, set, find) without -ing or -ed for action terms.
c_1b_4    noun        - Use singular form of nouns (user not users) for object and property terms.

c_1c__ roots          - Rules for root terms.
c_1c_1    type        - Use only approved root types from kernal_codename.txt, no custom roots without approval.
c_1c_2    action      - Use verb roots (get, set, find) for functions and methods that perform actions.
c_1c_3    object      - Use noun roots (user, data, config) for variables and properties that store values.
c_1c_4    file        - Use noun roots (user, data, config) for files and folders that contain related items.

c_1d__ context        - Rules for codename context.
c_1d_1    scope       - Match codename to its scope (global, local, private) to indicate visibility and access.
c_1d_2    purpose     - Match codename to its purpose (action, storage, configuration) to indicate function.
c_1d_3    location    - Match codename to its location (module, component, directory) to indicate position.

c_1e__ examples       - Example codename patterns.
c_1e_1    function    - get_user_data, set_config_value, find_active_users, update_user_status.
c_1e_2    variable    - user_name, config_value, active_users, current_status.
c_1e_3    file        - user_config, data_store, active_users, status_update.

